WEBVTT

00:00.066 --> 00:04.013
The blueprints are drafted, the workers are set.

00:05.756 --> 00:07.258
It's time to build his church.

00:08.220 --> 00:12.267
Our knees need to hit the ground in prayer before a shovel does.

00:13.349 --> 00:17.796
Our hands need to be raised in worship before they swing a hand.

00:19.239 --> 00:23.566
Let this church be more than a fellowship, more than a building.

00:23.586 --> 00:25.970
Let this church be a house of gold.

00:28.290 --> 00:29.172
That's all I've got.

00:29.372 --> 00:31.235
I'm ready to jump into the message.

00:31.896 --> 00:38.367
We're in the front line, the very beginning portion of a series that we started two weeks ago.

00:38.428 --> 00:43.156
It's a little confusing time period because we had Snowpalooza 26.

00:43.476 --> 00:44.498
You guys remember that?

00:44.802 --> 00:47.966
There's still a little remnants every now and again out in the field.

00:47.986 --> 00:56.936
There's a little pile of snow or something to remind us of days gone by and of cold winter times when Satan tried to freeze us from God, but praise God, we persevered.

00:57.257 --> 00:58.038
We made it through.

00:58.098 --> 01:07.829
We had a Friday night service that week and in that service, we kicked off a series that we're simply calling a house of prayer.

01:07.870 --> 01:09.431
Now we paused last week.

01:09.712 --> 01:11.634
We went back to the old series, but today,

01:11.778 --> 01:14.363
We are moving back into a house of prayer.

01:14.463 --> 01:17.229
Why is that important?

01:17.249 --> 01:25.746
Because if we do not become a house of prayer, then little to nothing that we attempt beyond that will be successful.

01:26.690 --> 01:29.853
Listen carefully, we can have the best speakers.

01:30.173 --> 01:31.955
We can have the best worship team.

01:32.255 --> 01:34.277
We can have the best children's ministry.

01:34.517 --> 01:36.379
We can serve the greatest coffee.

01:36.940 --> 01:39.122
We can have greeters that knock it out of the park.

01:39.342 --> 01:41.044
They surpass those from Walmart.

01:41.324 --> 01:43.786
I mean, we can have the best of everything.

01:44.067 --> 01:53.796
But if we're not people of prayer, if we're just trying to do this by ourselves, if we're attempting it in our own ability, in our own efforts with our own talent, guess what?

01:53.996 --> 01:56.018
Sooner than later, our talent

01:56.098 --> 01:56.939
runs out.

01:59.321 --> 01:59.702
Come on.

02:00.903 --> 02:08.791
Jesus himself said it this way, my house shall be called a house of prayer.

02:08.811 --> 02:15.958
Two weeks ago, when we had this Friday night service, I asked a very pertinent question, a vitally important question.

02:16.018 --> 02:20.743
The question of the message that day was this, do I have to pray?

02:22.264 --> 02:22.745
Do I have to?

02:22.865 --> 02:24.146
Well, the answer really is no.

02:25.154 --> 02:27.997
You don't have to pray, but you also don't have to eat.

02:28.618 --> 02:30.160
You also don't have to drink anything.

02:30.240 --> 02:31.521
You also don't have to breathe.

02:32.042 --> 02:36.407
There's a lot of things you don't have to do, but it's beneficial if you do them.

02:37.228 --> 02:38.229
Come on.

02:38.249 --> 02:50.002
And what we learned in that message two weeks ago is that it's not a fact of do I have to pray, but am I willing to engage in the opportunity that God has given to me?

02:50.562 --> 02:56.471
Am I willing to step into a conversation with the creator of the world?

02:56.511 --> 03:01.539
Am I willing to step into a moment of conversation with God?

03:02.280 --> 03:05.646
You see, prayer is not God demanding time from us.

03:06.768 --> 03:11.094
Prayer is God offering Himself to us.

03:12.557 --> 03:13.979
Come on.

03:13.999 --> 03:15.922
Jesus, when He died on the cross,

03:16.066 --> 03:22.295
The Bible says that the veil was torn and suddenly there was entrance into the holy of holies.

03:22.336 --> 03:25.941
There was entrance into the presence of God.

03:26.161 --> 03:30.328
No longer do we have to have a middleman that goes between us and God.

03:32.711 --> 03:37.539
But we can walk boldly into the presence of God.

03:38.300 --> 03:45.010
My goal of this series is that we will move from a people of just periodic

03:46.082 --> 03:54.374
short-term, momentary prayer will move beyond just rub it up, dub, thanks for the grub.

03:54.454 --> 03:55.756
Now I lay me down to sleep.

03:55.796 --> 04:07.052
I pray the Lord my soul to keep prayer and we'll move into a place where prayer becomes a regular daily part of our lives.

04:07.993 --> 04:11.378
In fact, the Bible says that we are to pray continuously.

04:12.482 --> 04:15.285
Now, in our own minds, that seems impossible, right?

04:15.325 --> 04:27.238
Because when we think prayer, we think closing our eyes and bellowing our heads and maybe kneeling or folding our hands or some posturing ourselves in some moments of reverence to God.

04:27.258 --> 04:29.761
And we're like, how do we accomplish that?

04:30.602 --> 04:38.491
When I've got a job, when I've got a family, when I have hobbies, when I have a day to attend to, how do I pray continuously?

04:38.711 --> 04:41.234
How do I pray without ceasing?

04:42.082 --> 04:48.070
Basically what that means is I leave the receiver off and I just spend time with God.

04:48.110 --> 05:10.802
Do you remember, come on, those of you from my generation, those of you that had a phone cord connected to the wall that was long enough to reach to the back of the house and close the door so you could talk to your girl when you were in high school and mom and dad couldn't talk to you in that moment, but when you got done, when you hung up the phone and you walked out, they said, who was that?

05:12.770 --> 05:15.633
Come on, some of you remember those days.

05:16.274 --> 05:26.045
Some of you remember the moment where you left the phone off the receiver, and it sat there, and you just talked to one another, and you would say things like this, no, you hang up.

05:27.226 --> 05:28.347
No, you hang up.

05:28.728 --> 05:35.255
And finally, one of you would get sick and tired, and you would go, and you hang up the phone, and then you would answer for it the next day, right?

05:36.797 --> 05:41.362
Praying without ceasing is that moment of leaving the phone

05:42.530 --> 05:46.476
off the receiver and just spending time with God.

05:47.737 --> 06:10.450
I remember when my daughter was in college, well, the truth but told she still does it to this day, but she'll call in the evenings and right now she calls, she works at a hospital in Springfield, she's an RN there and as she leaves the hospital and she makes her trek through numerous parking lots to get to her vehicle, she will call and just talk.

06:11.778 --> 06:16.225
When she was in high school even college, there were moments she would be walking around the store.

06:16.585 --> 06:21.513
She'd be shopping, but she just wanted mom or just wanted dad on the other side of the line.

06:21.553 --> 06:24.177
She just wanted to be with us.

06:25.599 --> 06:28.804
See, that's what God's asking of us today.

06:29.865 --> 06:33.871
Will you just spend your day with me?

06:35.754 --> 06:38.258
Will you make my house

06:39.170 --> 06:44.155
What we're talking about here is it's not, let's make encounter church a house of prayer.

06:44.876 --> 06:51.083
You see, that's the result of personal lives making themselves a house of prayer.

06:51.463 --> 06:54.867
The Bible says that we are the temple of the Holy Spirit.

06:55.047 --> 07:01.354
We are the house, the resident of the Holy Spirit.

07:01.374 --> 07:05.458
We are to make his house a house of prayer.

07:05.826 --> 07:24.033
and the result of we, his people, gathering together in our personal time, in corporate time, and spending time lifting him up and honoring him of making this house a house a prayer, suddenly this house becomes a house a prayer.

07:25.496 --> 07:28.700
So I'm gonna spend the next five weeks.

07:29.742 --> 07:32.466
We're gonna talk about numerous topics today.

07:32.546 --> 07:39.755
We're going to simply talk about the what, the why, the how of prayer, of having a conversation with God.

07:39.795 --> 07:40.056
Why?

07:40.216 --> 07:45.803
Because we have free access to the creator of the world.

07:47.185 --> 07:49.728
This isn't just a moment of obligation.

07:49.748 --> 07:54.034
Well, now that I gave my heart and my life to Christ, I have to pray.

07:55.522 --> 07:59.507
And if I don't pray, then somehow God's gonna smite me from heaven.

07:59.527 --> 08:02.952
He's gonna take his God-sized thumb and press it down on the earth.

08:02.992 --> 08:11.423
And I'm gonna go, so we feel guilty because we haven't spent time with God.

08:13.145 --> 08:17.851
It's not a religious obligation, but rather it's an invitation.

08:17.931 --> 08:22.898
It's a direct line of access to God.

08:24.002 --> 08:28.637
So rather than asking the question, do I have to pray, the better question might be this.

08:28.938 --> 08:32.690
Why wouldn't I when the door's already been open?

08:34.018 --> 08:39.022
Why wouldn't I engage in conversation with the King of Kings and the Lord of Lords?

08:39.062 --> 08:43.366
Why wouldn't I have conversation with the creator of the world?

08:43.426 --> 09:04.004
Why wouldn't I have conversation with the one that spoke my life into existence, the one who knew me by name when I was in my mama's belly, the one that already knows every detail of my life, the one who was concerned about the details of my life, the one that wants to walk with me and promises that he will never leave me

09:03.984 --> 09:09.811
Why wouldn't I want to have conversation with Him?

09:11.453 --> 09:18.621
But sometimes we avoid prayer because if we're being honest, we feel like we just don't know how.

09:21.264 --> 09:23.627
Would you agree with me today that prayer is important?

09:24.748 --> 09:31.095
I'd venture to say that most of us, if not all of us in the room, would agree that prayer is important.

09:31.496 --> 09:33.298
We believe that it matters

09:33.762 --> 09:38.548
